                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/6617: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-09-25T11:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 25, 1925—11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received September 25—3:26 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>416. Following from American consul general at Canton:</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“September 21, 4 p.m. General Hsu Chung-chi has been relieved of his command
                        and left hurriedly during the night on a vessel bound for Shanghai. His
                        bodyguard was disarmed by order of the commander of the Whampoa Cadets. It
                        is reported that General Hsu’s principal military assistant with the
                        Cantonese army near Sheklung has revolted and will join Chen Chiung-ming’s
                        forces in eastern Kwangtung.</p>
                    <p>The so-called diplomatic committee has left for Shanghai.</p>
                    <p>Line between the Reds and Moderates now becoming clearly defined. There are
                        indications that the opposition in outlying districts is crystallizing
                        against the Reds.”</p>
                </quote>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
